We love answering GSAP-related questions, but in order to get you a fast, accurate answer it is very important that you **provide code we can *test***.

Your problem may be related to CSS, HTML, a framework or JavaScript (or a mixture of those). A tiny code snippet (outside of its context), is difficult to diagnose. We need code that we can dig into and play with...quickly.

We are big fans of [CodePen.io](https://codepen.io),Â an online editor that allows you to create (and share) demos that areÂ easy toÂ inspect andÂ edit. They make isolating issues much faster.

**Watch How it is Done:**

**GSAP 3 Starter Pen:**

[https://codepen.io/GreenSock/pen/VoZNxw](https://codepen.io/GreenSock/pen/aYYOdN)

**To create a demo with all of GSAP including every bonus plugin**:

1. Click the **Edit on CodePen**button
2. Click the **Fork**button to create your own copy (lower right corner).
3. Add the minimal amount of HTML, CSS and JavaScript necessary to replicate your issue.
4. Save the pen
5. Paste the URL of your pen (demo) into a new forum topic with a short description of the problem.
6. Include OS, browser and device information where applicable.

CodePen is completely free to use and you don't even have to sign up or log in. We do recommend [creating a free account](https://codepen.io/signup) as it will allow you to save and organize your pens and much more.

**Using a framework/library like React, Vue, Next, etc.?**

CodePen isn't always ideal for these tools, so here are some [Stackblitz starter templates](https://stackblitz.com/@gsap-dev/collections) that you can fork and import the [gsap-trial NPM package](https://gsap.com/trial):

* [React](https://stackblitz.com/@gsap-dev/collections/gsap-react-starters)Â (*please* read [this article](https://gsap.com/react)!)
